arXiv:2505.19123v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: In this paper, we investigate the CP asymmetries ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{pm}$ and ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{mp}$ in $B_{c}^{\pm}ightarrow B^{\pm} K^{0}+B^{\pm} { ar{K}}^0ightarrow B^{\pm} \pi^{\pm} e^{\mp} 
u_{e}$ and $B_{c}^{\pm}ightarrow B^{\pm} K^{0}+B^{\pm} { ar{K}}^0ightarrow B^{\pm} \pi^{\mp} e^{\pm} 
u_{e}$ decays, both of them consist of three parts: the indirect CP violations in $K^0 - ar{K}^0$ mixing $A_{CP,mix}^{pm}$ and $A_{CP,mix}^{mp}$, the direct CP violations in $B_{c}$ decay $A_{CP,dir}^{pm}$ and $A_{CP,dir}^{mp}$, the new CP violation effects $A_{CP,int}^{pm}$ and $A_{CP,int}^{mp}$, which originate from the interference between the amplitude of the $B_{c}^{-}ightarrow B^{-} K^{0} ({ ar{K}}^0) ightarrow B^{-} \pi^{-} e^{+} 
u_{e}(\pi^{+} e^{-}  ar{
u}_{e})$ decay with the difference between the oscillating effect of $K^0ightarrow { ar{K}}^0$ and that of ${ ar{K}}^0ightarrow K^0 $. The strong phase differences of the direct CP asymmetries $A_{CP,dir}^{pm}$ and $A_{CP,dir}^{mp}$ arising from $K^0- ar{K}^0$ mixing parameters. ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{pm}$ and ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{mp}$ are of the order $\mathcal{O}(10^{-4})$ and $\mathcal{O}(10^{-3})$, respectively. The new CP violation effect ${\mathcal A}_{CP,int}^{pm}$ plays a dominant role in ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{pm}$, the CP asymmetry ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{mp}$ is dominated by the indirect CP violation ${\mathcal A}_{CP,mix}^{mp}$, so the CP asymmetry ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{pm}$ provides an ideal place to study the new CP violation effect. We derive another two asymmetry observables ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{pp}$ and ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{mm}$, which are dominated by $K^0- ar{K}^0$ mixing. The observables ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{pm}$, ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{mp}$, ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{pp}$ and ${\mathcal A}_{CP}^{mm}$ are hopefully to be marginally observed at the LHC experiment and the HL-LHC experiment.
